text.tspan: Sprinkle chicken with 1/8 teaspoon each salt and pepper.
Heat sun-dried tomato oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the chicken and
cook, turning once, until browned and an instant-read thermometer inserted into
the thickest part registers 165 degrees F, about 6 minutes total. Transfer to a plate.
Add sun-dried tomatoes and shallots to the pan. Cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Increase heat to high and add wine. Cook, scraping up any browned bits, until the
liquid has mostly evaporated, about 2 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium and stir in cream, any accumulated juices from the chicken
and the remaining 1/8 teaspoon each salt and pepper; simmer for 2 minutes.
Return the chicken to the pan and turn to coat with the sauce. Serve the chicken
topped with the sauce and parsley.
